t9JudxLq5Rj463LdKiegotPOL91vR364wDmVWWQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test approach**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the tests need to execute natively. The existing ObjectImporter test catches unsupported cases for defineClass, but maybe we shouldn't catch anything unless there's an actual error. Adding a catch for Error with a helper for Native seems fine, but if it’s a JVM Error, it would rethrow. If there's a native UnsupportedFeatureError at export, the test passes for native, yet JVM is still covered. Do I need to include NativeImageSupport import? Only if I'm catching it, but is that too broad?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking methods and packages**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I should add methods inherited from the Object class to be excluded. It seems fine, but I also need to check if the `javassist_javassist` package has a user-code filter. I want to make sure I'm covering all bases to ensure proper functionality and performance. Let's see what the requirements are for filtering in this context, as it's important to avoid complications down the line.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VBiQRHGSMnuT239Tswl1Fe8F|fc_03466d1b8f067e720169f50bcc45d4819fb06156248073bb47", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1746, "output": 1103, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31521, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777667001640, "responseId": "resp_03466d1b8f067e720169f50bba1724819faa9712e592ff3e08"}}
