[thinking] I'm thinking about how our catch for the entire test might handle UnsupportedFeatureError if there’s a serialization issue with native features. Native serialization supports metadata, but if metadata is missing, it might lead to a MissingSerializationRegistrationError. I wonder if `isUnsupportedFeatureError` checks for that specific error; it seems more related to `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError`. Also, was serialization of dynamically generated objects included? The broad catch might be questionable, so perhaps I should narrow it down to exportObject instead.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
